00:46:56.700 --> 00:46:59.100
And I'm dealing with economics.

00:46:59.100 --> 00:47:04.050
And there's a mechanics that
is, as a result of this,

00:47:04.050 --> 00:47:09.990
leading to two economies.

00:47:09.990 --> 00:47:14.070
So they're hidden in the
economic numbers, the averages.

00:47:14.070 --> 00:47:16.930
If you want to go on
LinkedIn, I wrote two pieces

00:47:16.930 --> 00:47:19.330
that you might find
interesting on LinkedIn.

00:47:19.330 --> 00:47:24.730
I divided the top 40% from
the bottom 60%, the majority

00:47:24.730 --> 00:47:27.370
of people, and I looked
at, what is the economy

00:47:27.370 --> 00:47:29.670
of the majority of people like?

00:47:29.670 --> 00:47:31.810
And if you were to
look at that economy,

00:47:31.810 --> 00:47:33.580
it is a terrible economy.

00:47:33.580 --> 00:47:35.890
It has not grown.

00:47:35.890 --> 00:47:38.530
It's the only population
