01:10:51.580 --> 01:10:52.290
I couldn't do it.

01:10:52.290 --> 01:10:54.130
[LAUGHTER]

01:10:54.130 --> 01:10:55.930
So it's a personal choice.

01:10:55.930 --> 01:10:58.150
If you feel that's
important, you

01:10:58.150 --> 01:11:00.370
will then gravitate
to organizations

01:11:00.370 --> 01:11:03.160
that are more idea
meritocratic, and evolution

01:11:03.160 --> 01:11:05.440
will take its course, both
because of the entrepreneur

01:11:05.440 --> 01:11:07.132
and because the
individual's doing that.

01:11:07.132 --> 01:11:08.590
JORDAN THIBODEAU:
I'm going to take

01:11:08.590 --> 01:11:10.720
an online question real quick.

01:11:10.720 --> 01:11:12.610
Measurement is a big
theme in your book.

01:11:12.610 --> 01:11:14.200
How do you approach
measuring teams

01:11:14.200 --> 01:11:16.840
whose work has only
second order effects--

01:11:16.840 --> 01:11:19.360
for example, product
aesthetics or who

01:11:19.360 --> 01:11:21.110
prevent bad things
from happening so you

01:11:21.110 --> 01:11:23.020
don't have the counterfactuals?

01:11:23.020 --> 01:11:28.060
RAY DALIO: OK, I want
to say that in every one

01:11:28.060 --> 01:11:32.870
of these types of
questions in which there

01:11:32.870 --> 01:11:37.770
is a particular dilemma
or problem to solve,

01:11:37.770 --> 01:11:42.480
it starts off with a
mind or a group of minds

01:11:42.480 --> 01:11:45.330
thinking, how do I
solve that problem?

01:11:48.020 --> 01:11:52.880
And doing that in an
idea meritocratic way

01:11:52.880 --> 01:11:58.250
will give you the best answer
to solving that problem.

01:11:58.250 --> 01:12:01.250
And that is the most
important thing.

01:12:01.250 --> 01:12:04.630
So when I'm asked
that question, I

01:12:04.630 --> 01:12:08.410
might give my particular
answer to the question.

01:12:08.410 --> 01:12:11.500
But if I just gave my particular
answer to the question,

01:12:11.500 --> 01:12:16.630
I wouldn't convey the fact that
you have the power individually

01:12:16.630 --> 01:12:18.930
to do that anyway.

01:12:18.930 --> 01:12:22.505
So we all face that question.

01:12:22.505 --> 01:12:24.630
When you have a group and
you take the second order

01:12:24.630 --> 01:12:30.150
consequences, and how do you
know the decomposition of that?

01:12:30.150 --> 01:12:33.480
OK, well we can take a
little test here of sorts,

01:12:33.480 --> 01:12:35.160
and we can take
each person's ideas

01:12:35.160 --> 01:12:36.780
and say, OK, now we
have to figure out

01:12:36.780 --> 01:12:39.240
the best way to do that.

01:12:39.240 --> 01:12:42.030
And we can then
gather those best ways

01:12:42.030 --> 01:12:47.340
and come up with that best
way, and that is the path.

01:12:47.340 --> 01:12:48.660
That's always the path.

01:12:48.660 --> 01:12:51.450
If you understand that path,
you'll get to the best way

01:12:51.450 --> 01:12:54.660
you can get to, and that's
better than the ways

01:12:54.660 --> 01:12:55.300
that you have.

01:12:55.300 --> 01:12:56.850
And then it becomes clear.

01:12:56.850 --> 01:13:01.650
So then, in our
particular case, there

01:13:01.650 --> 01:13:05.760
is a series of evaluations
that are very clear evaluations

01:13:05.760 --> 01:13:09.150
that people make themselves,
in a believability way, about

01:13:09.150 --> 01:13:10.810
all dimensions of that.

01:13:10.810 --> 01:13:16.274
So sometimes you can
measure results directly.

01:13:16.274 --> 01:13:18.690
In other words, you can measure
somebody's batting average

01:13:18.690 --> 01:13:20.400
or something-- the equivalent.

01:13:20.400 --> 01:13:25.230
And sometimes it
needs a critique.

01:13:25.230 --> 01:13:29.460
If we're asking does somebody
sing better than somebody else,

01:13:29.460 --> 01:13:32.400
there's no quantitative measure
for that type of measure

01:13:32.400 --> 01:13:35.610
to see that, but we could sort
of say they're critiquing.

01:13:35.610 --> 01:13:40.300
So such measures can
happen at all levels.

01:13:40.300 --> 01:13:42.240
And so we do that.

01:13:42.240 --> 01:13:45.399
Whatever the measurements
that we come up with jointly,

01:13:45.399 --> 01:13:47.190
and we think, OK, that's
good measurements,

01:13:47.190 --> 01:13:49.350
we can create metrics about it.

01:13:49.350 --> 01:13:52.985
So qualitative things--

01:13:52.985 --> 01:13:55.260
I give the example, populism.

01:13:55.260 --> 01:13:56.700
Well, how do I measure?

01:13:56.700 --> 01:13:59.320
But populism happens
over and over again.

01:13:59.320 --> 01:14:00.870
It's a qualitative thing.

01:14:00.870 --> 01:14:04.170
But I could start to
create that process.

01:14:04.170 --> 01:14:07.320
I've found that, by and
large, almost anything

01:14:07.320 --> 01:14:12.440
that I can think of I can
express in an algorithm,

01:14:12.440 --> 01:14:13.320
in a rule.

01:14:13.320 --> 01:14:17.610
The real question is, how do
you get to that good rule?

01:14:17.610 --> 01:14:19.780
JORDAN THIBODEAU: Excellent.

