that's 60% correlated,

01:32:50.500 --> 01:32:53.940
and I put more than 10
in, the marginal benefits

01:32:53.940 --> 01:32:57.540
of diversification are
virtually nil, so that you're

01:32:57.540 --> 01:33:00.330
going to have the stock
market or something like that.

01:33:00.330 --> 01:33:04.890
And then some alpha is the
deviation relative to that.

01:33:04.890 --> 01:33:08.250
Whereas, if you have
an asset class--

01:33:08.250 --> 01:33:09.870
different asset classes--

01:33:09.870 --> 01:33:12.640
they'll behave very
uncorrelated with that.

01:33:12.640 --> 01:33:16.680
And so portfolio construction
based on capital allocation,

01:33:16.680 --> 01:33:19.320
